						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the Lōkanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 16th century.</p>						

						<p>It is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Nandana, Āśvija śu. 1.</hi> These details are insufficient for verification.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift to the blacksmith Habōja, son of Pāpōja probably by the carpenter Nala Timmōja, son of Aṅkōja. The record is badly damaged and the details are, therefore, lost. </p>						

						</summary>
